                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The overall value of expansions has definitely gone down in my opinion.  Kunark and Velious were like, cool, we're getting entirely new continents with all this new content to explore for every type of player.  Luclin, getting a little weird, inventing a moon that somehow is invisible from the planet it orbits and an entire race managed to go through space and land on it and survive, ok, this game isn't a physics simulation, and at least its lore was somehow related to the rest of Norrath and it still has a lot of content, same for PoP, but LDoN, LoY, these seem to have no relation whatsoever to the rest of the game and rely less on actual content than on gimmicks like the map feature to sell.  (And I won't get into the instancing argument but you can imagine what I think about it.)  Also, didn't Kunark cost something like $17 shipped? (albeit without a game box, and possibly 2 weeks late, but at least you got a physical CD instead of download-only)  Now you're paying more in some cases for less in all of them.  Maybe I'm just one of those complaining ex-players who doesn't get it.
<br />

<br />
I do, however, have to give SOE credit that recently they seem to be listening to the players much better (forums are back, the summit), so we'll see if they actually follow through and make some changes.  For the sake of everyone still playing I hope Smedley is telling the truth and they will fix current problems before releasing yet another expansion.  That's always been an issue but at least the old expansions tended to replace all of the old problems with new problems rather than adding more.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
