                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It seems to me he is basically saying not that LDoN sucks, but that the lore behind it does.  On that I'd say he's right on the money, the Wayfarer Brotherhood lore is the most pathetic story telling I've seen out of EQ.  My other complaint with it is the dungeons are so boring and unimaginative that spending enough time there to get enough points for stuff is simply a chore.  They could have done more to make it interesting, like have junctures in the crawl where you've got to solve something to open a path to you and depending on the solution it opens a different path.  The possibilities with instanced dungeons are almost limitless and LDoN really takes the easy way out.
<br />

<br />
Now, don't throw tomatos, but I love Luclin <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" />  The art, the encounters and especially the Combine Empire lore are awesome.  VT is actually an exception to this, and the million hp boss mobs are just a bore.  But overall, its my second favorite behind PoP.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=515779" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://lunapark.org/~luna/mithrasig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
