                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Seriously, revamp old zones. I've been hearing of Veeshan's Peak getting a revamp for 3 years now for example.
<br />

<br />
Hell while waiting for raids to start I sometimes do something you wouldn't normally do: Get a SoW or drink a Blood of the Wolf potion, take a PoK book to Qeynos and RUN from there to Freeport...on FOOT...and hell, North Karana, /who and it turns up 1 player, me. Who the hell goes to Splitpaw? King Xorbbs gorge? Let's exclude Highhold for the moment as it's an excellent twink xp area. Lake Rathe? What? Now you can add most of Kunark to this aswell I suppose. Aside from those who farm Kunark spells in Sebilis noone goes there. Oh to kill Trakannon for teeth or the mini-Trak for bard epic. Upgrade the loot there, bring it to VT level, hell even EP level. Dalnir? Upgrade that zone, damn fun zone. Expand the Sarnak fortress in LoIO, make it a seperate zone, some easy lore to add like they're rebelling against Chardok. Put 100hp/mana + nice stat gear in there. It doesn't need to be raid material either. Something for the masses.
<br />

<br />
Involve ALL current expansions in large quests, not quite epic, but the rewards would be at VT level. You could include factions again where you choose either Dorf, Dragon or Giant faction when you hit the Velious phase of that quest. Three possible outcomes (more if you make it split along 'good/evil/neutral' races, deities etc). Grand robe of the Oracle is a small step in that direction, reasonable reward too, but too simple.
<br />

<br />
There are millions of possibilities when you figure Luclin in. That expansion's monumental failure was the fact that there was no real story to it...aside from the massive timesinks. Yeah the fall of the Combine empire followed by a jealous dude. You had Seru vs the Kerrans, but the rest of it was thrown together basicly. The VT quest and Ssra have no connection to it at all really, except the planes rift which Emperor Ssraeszha drops for you to complete the key to VT. It wasn't fleshed out. Luclin is a skeleton. The lore is disjointed and where the hell is Luclin herself? What happened to the Akheva, where do the big ass worms fit in? You see their traces everywhere, you know, those round tunnels connecting a lot of zones. Why is Emperor Ssraeszha the destroyer of Gods? Who did he kill yo?
<br />

<br />
The sleeper went back to sleep too it seems. He's awake on all servers as far as I know...maybe not on Morden Rasp server (?). He murdered Yelinak and some random stuff in NToV but disappeared from knowledge after that. Or is he reserved for EQ2?
<br />

<br />
The level 65 population is growing daily now that levelling up isn't hard anymore. But the content is still the same. Building on what you have now is better than creating new stuff on the fly. And a six week hiatus from releasing the next expansion will be a drop in the ocean. The lvl 65 population is congregating in PoP and in 1 zone, BoT, 2 of you count PoValor. I don't think that even if the EPs were opened up at some point that that would solve a damn thing because it's only 4 new zones with little to offer the majority of the lvl 65s, just more xp. Instead of 1 zone you spread it over 5 zones, 4 of which aren't meant for this in the first place.
<br />

<br />
You need to go back and look at the places I mentioned among others, spread us out over all Norrath and break the monotony.
<br />

<br />
But fix the bugs first.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">S a g e F u n x i</span>.Legendary.tribunal
