                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Every now and then they revamp a zone, people oooh and ahhh at it for 2 weeks, then go right back to thier favorite zone.  It would be nice if they did some massive revamps on the old content, but I got the feeling that BoT would still stay unflagged levelers paradise.  I think, if they revamped the zones, they should be BoT level zones for non EP equiped players, but thats just me, cause I'm not EP flagged.  Once you have EP access a lot more avenues open up, but BoT is the end all for those of us who seldom raid.
<br />

<br />
Personally I thought Kunark was the hight of EQ story telling and lore.  Kunark lore just fit better with the existing story from the original EQ.  Velious, on the other hand, was mostly new, made up stuff to accondimate for the presence of big raid monsters to kill.  But at least they bothered in Velious.  Luclin story pretty poor, but again, at least they tried.  The Combine link was a stab in the right direction, but they failed to go into sufficent depth with it beyond explaining why there are two cities and spires that port you to the moon.
<br />

<br />
Another faction based progression like Velious is a waste of time.  I always said, I'm an equal oportunity Velious killer, and so is anyone else who was serious about raiding back in those days.  Nobody cares about the factions beyond which one drops the nicest loot you can handle.  Most everyone in the Velious era probably spent time on all three, and then none at all.  I would like to see a faction progression where you were stuck with what you picked, then it might be cool. 
<br />

<br />
PoP?  Well all the gods exist for phat lewting now, who cares why, the time for stories is beyond us.
<br />

<br />
