                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree in general with the above post.   It has some good points.  And it's right about the LDoN storyline to some extent (Especially Rujarkian hills, the special "gee, theres been a race of orcs buried here for hundreds of years and no one noticed" zone.)   Though I rather like the extensions of lore for Mistmoore and Guk.  There is a bit of a storyline here, but it's doled out in tiny little fragments as you do hundreds of adventures.   LDoN was a decent expansion that could have been a freakin' amazing one.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> Luclin, getting a little weird, inventing a moon that somehow is invisible from the planet it orbits and an entire race managed to go through space and land on it and survive, ok, this game isn't a physics simulation, and at least its lore was somehow related to the rest of Norrath and it still has a lot of content, same for PoP, but LDoN, LoY, these seem to have no relation whatsoever to the rest of the game and rely less on actual content than on gimmicks like the map feature to sell.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
A couple of issues with this post - Luclin has EXCELLENT lore.  It's not easy to find, but the storylines are fabulous.   The problem is that it was never -finished- as an expansion.  The entire city of Sanctus Seru is basically empty - there are dozens upon dozens of NPCs that don't even respond to a hail.   The situation is similar in Katta Castellum - these two cities could have been the luclin equivalents to Skyshrine and Kael Drakkel, but they were never completed.  There's bits and scraps of unfinished quests ALL OVER the place on Luclin.   I always joke that the next expansion should be "Lost Content of Luclin" and a friend of mine theorizes that the strange glyphs on the walls of Ssra say "Dear Sony, please finish our expansion." in Shissar.  
<br />

<br />
Also, for those of you who seem to feel like LoY has no tie ins to the EQ storyline - LoY fleshes out the map; Broken Skull Rock has been on the EQ map since the original game, but it's always been one of those places where you just couldn't go (Kinda like those massive plains that're supposed to be on Faydwer somewhere. o.o ) LoY added it and filled it in with what is, to me, entertaining and well wrought content.
<br />

<br />
But anyway. Nitpicking aside, the Necro-forums post above hits the nail close enough to the head for me. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
