<br />

<br />
I'm not sure what remains to finish here - Grieg was one of the geomancers who helped Seru come to Luclin, but he was unable to figure out how to get BACK.  He retreated to the 'city' now known as Grieg's End to work on that very issue (Hence all the portal spires and the like scattered throughout the zone), but Luclin herself, for reasons known only to her, took it upon herself to send agents to drive him mad. Which they did.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> The snakes fit, but there's no way to look at thier culture from the inside--a terrible omission IMHO.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Ironically, I always felt the Shissar were one of the great "where the heck did this come from?" points of Luclin.  But if you feel they fit, then keen - obviously they worked for someone.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> I feel like Luclin had the best potential for being the best expansion, but it got ruined by being too big to ever finish.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure it's really -that- much more complex than Velious, really.  Katta and Seru are much like Kael and Skyshrine, and Grieg's storyline bears some resemblance to Velketor's.    I really think that it could have been a kick ass expansion, but it needed a few more months in the pot. (And not the "oh ****! They're banging on the doors to Vex Thall already" pot. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> )  Though it didn't help that they were doing all that technical junk with the game at the same time (New graphics engine, new playable race, new class, focus items, skill mod items, etc.)
<br />

<br />
Oh well. By the very fact that we're having this conversation, one can tell that Luclin had and could have had an excellent chunk of lore.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
	<tr>
