                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Though I think the zones need a revamp in general, I disagree that they all need to be made high level content.  I point at Cazic Thule as an example.  Pre-nerf, er, revamp, that zone was my favorite for 27 to 30+ leveling.  It was an awesome proving ground for single group mechanics and it was rarely underpopulated.  Now?  I find 2 or 3 farmers in there, maybe a group doing the ring quest and other than that, it's empty.  The difference?  It's not overpowered for the level range it's pointed at, but, underpowered for 65s to farm it for the drops that are too rare but still popular.  Ie: You can level faster in another zone for faster, or better, rewards (BoT) so, why hang out here?  CT is a classic example of a good idea gone BAD.  My suspicion is they did this because OT was draining the 30s and they thought CT was underutilized because of it... well, other zones are STILL cricially underutilized: Najena, Befallen, Runnyeye and Blackburrow come very readily to mind.  But, if you revamp them, don't make them all 60+ zones... that's catering to the ubers again... make them fun and different and useable by a variety of levels.  Balance the risks and the rewards so that they are entertaining rather than tedious.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />GnarliAnna
<br />
E65.60/CT h+ 1.807khp 4.01km ft8 G++&lt;3 e++(+++) o++ T+++(+++++) L+ H++(+++) f++ g b@ c++ t+++ D++ X++</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
